data.title: Good for dinner and a drink
data.text: While staying at the Embassy Suites Hotel which is in the same facility as Cork's; had dinner during a business trip.  Ate in the bar area which was comfortable with good food.  Will return if in the hotel again.

data.title: Good food, reasonable price
data.text: Ordered the grilled salmon for takeout. Fish done perfectly with nice side of very fresh, not over cooked string beans and potatoes. Ordered small side salad with Caesar dressing - delicious.

data.title: Convenient, Reasonable, Friendly
data.text: Attached to the Embassy Suites, it's pretty much holding us captive.  Thankfully, the food is good and the service is great!  Menu is typical, but tasty (love the fish bites).  Bar white wine is Ecco Domani so I'm good!

data.title: Mediocrity is Thy Name
data.text: Here on a business trip with limited time so ate here twice (staying in the hotel where it's located). I want to like this place, the servers are really nice, it has a nice atmosphere but I don't know what to make of the food. First time I ordered the wings, I noticed it said braised so I asked and was told they were then fried so I asked for extra crispy. I have to say the flavor was good but they were not wings in the way I expected, tasty but disappointing but I chalked it up to being a Midwestern thing. Come back two days later, ordered the grilled meatloaf and about gagged. It was dry, tasteless and smothered in BBQ sauce I'm sure was procured from the SISCO deli #10 can. It was accompanied by the most pathetic mashed potatoes I've ever had...ever! Ever...nasty bad! To be fair, the server was great and she removed the meal charge and I tipped as if I ate the meal but the manager never came by, if he had I might have added a star but as far as I'm concerned, he was the failure and I won't be back...ever.

data.title: Great service
data.text: I only came here for drinks and dessert but I saw a few things on the menu that I would have tried if we were there for an actual meal. I was more than happy with the Irish cream cheesecake I got and I enjoyed the emerald fizz martini as well. I wouldn't go out of my way to come back but if I am in the area again I will most likely stop back because we received great service from our waiter and the manager.

data.title: Standard Irish Bar
data.text: This is located inside the Embassy Suites in Downtown St. Paul. The decor is exactly what you would expect from an "Irish" pub in America. The bar itself is restively crammed, and there isn't a whole lot of space to move about. Drinks are pretty good, I didn't not order or taste any of the food. Pretty good place to grab a drink and relax in the afternoon hours as it will likely be pretty empty.

data.title: Irish luck, no Barlarney
data.text: This past Tuesday, six of us had tickets for a function at the Fitzgerald theater. We chose Cork's for dinner because it had off-street parking and was close to the "Fitz". Our Irish luck was in full gear when we ordered starters of chicken legs with bleu cheese sauce, spinach dip with crostinis, and wine all around at Happy Hour prices. Again our Irish luck kicked in because Tuesday night is half-price on any Irish dishes. So, corned beef and cabbage was a bargain and was served in generous portions. The fish and chips were great - just enough fish but could have used a little more coleslaw. Our waitress was fantastic; however, service was a little slow, but the six of us had much to talk about. Even without Irish luck, we will return again.

data.title: A wee bit of Irish
data.text: Was staying at the hotel and arrived late/don't know the area so decided to try the in house restaurant. There was an amazing array of choices in terms of libations and food. I had the fish & chips that were lightly and beautifully battered with a nice tartar sauce. The fries were underwhelming but the cole slaw (though slight in its portion) was terrific. Prices were incredibly reasonable and it's a good place to go if you aren't interested in exploring the area when you arrive late.

data.title: Many good meals
data.text: My trial team and I were in the Embassy Suites, where Cork's is located, for almost a month, and so ate many a meal in this nice mid-range restaurant. The servers were always friendly, although the kitchen was sometimes a little slow when busy. Cork's has a nice selection of down to earth fare, like fish and chips, Shepard's pie, and meat loaf. Prices are reasonable and the atmosphere is welcoming.

data.title: After game fare!
data.text: Stopped in after the hockey game for a quick bite to eat.  Food was good, but the wait staff was overly busy and service was slow due to the high number of patrons.

data.title: Huge Salads
data.text: We're staying at the Embassy Suites where Cork's is located, so we've eaten there several times.  I've had the hamburger sliders, the fish sandwich and the large salad with chicken.  The salad was huge and filled with ingredients including blue cheese crumbles, bacon, etc.  The service has always been fast and the wait staff friendly.

data.title: Excellence
data.text: Try the drunken broil.  One of my favorite guilty pleasures - Jameson's gravy and mint peas. All of the food is excellent. Servis is excellent.

data.title: Always consistent
data.text: They don't have a gluten free or dairy free menu, but the chef can make the adjustments to satisfy me.  The staff is very good about keeping on top of it and communicating well with the chef. After a long travel and work day it's nice to KNOW I can count on. Good meal and great friendly staff.

data.title: Excellent wings
data.text: I ordered the wings and was pleasantly surprised. The Cajun dry rub was delicious.  Very convenient when staying at the Embassy Suites.

data.title: Irish Roots Alive and Well Here! Beautiful Hotel BTW.
data.text:
Well themed Irish pub. Dark woods, brick, lots of beer and liquor choices. Standard pub fare. Fish and chips, shepherds pie, and Reubens.

We had the fish and chips and pot pie. Pot pie is not your average pie, more stylish and ritzy. The fish and chips were OK, kinda stale and cold. Tartar sauce was good. One thing that annoyed me was the coleslaw, about 2 tablespoons of it in a tiny cup...really?

The worst thing though was that service was very slow. It was busy and our waitress seemed to be everywhere, but there seemed like there was plenty of staff so I'm not sure what happened there. Oh well!

data.title: Great team event at Cork's!
data.text: Went with my work team for an after work event at Cork's.  They couldn't have been more accommodating!  The food was great, reasonably priced, and our wait person, Bam, was spot on.  All of us had a wonderful time.  We will be back and soon!

owner_response.author: Jacob S, Manager at Cork's Irish Pub, responded to this review
owner_response.text:
Hey Kathy!
We're so glad you enjoyed your time with us at Cork's.
I hope you'll remember your neighbors up here the next time you and your team decide to go out and have a great time. 
Hope to see you again soon!
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: That's a tall?
data.text: Drinks are a little small for the price but it is very convenient if you're saying in the hotel. Though I haven't tried their food it does smell good.

data.title: Scottish Eggs and Drinks
data.text: I went here with my wife later in the evening while we were staying at the attached Embassy Suites.  We tried Scottish Eggs for our first time.  They were good I can't say its the best ever but we enjoyed them.  The prices are fair given they are attached to a hotel.

data.title: It's handy
data.text:
Perhaps waiting 25 minutes should have set off some red lights. The food is mediocre at best but just uninviting. 
Overall a meh.

data.title: Very good-try the Walleye
data.text:
We had lunch and late night desserts while staying at Embassy Suites on Aug. 29. 
I had the walleye sandwich which was excellent, and my friend had the chicken basket-hand carved white chicken.  Also, we had their Irish Cream Crème Brulee and Cheesecake-both were terrific.   Service was personal and prompt.
